4 hours is generally considered about the average for the quest if you stop to grab the items while you're talking to the NPCs instead of waiting until you have the list of items at the end of the quest.<br>
While I have heard of the Shin Lord, on VERY rare occasions, dropping two Ghoulbanes in a row, I've heard a lot more stories of people camping for over 24 hours and still not having a Ghoulbane to show for it.<br>
If you're of high enough level to solo the Shin Lord and the room he's in (which is typically full of healers), then you're definitely high enough level to solo the quest.<br>
